Course Description:
(Prerequisite: Placement at 300 level on Phase II placement exam, grade of ‘C’ or better in SPAN B301, or consent of instructor. Department consent
required for transfer students.) Interpretation of contemporary Hispanic culture through selected Spanish or Spanish-American films. A: Spanish film;
B: Spanish-American film. Taught in Spanish. (Satisfies USCB General Education Global Citizenship and Multicultural Understanding Requirement).
